tm:topic_2 a tm:Topic;
rdfs:comment "A topic is a FrAC observation that groups observable lexical forms (OntoLex Forms) and is observed in a corpus."@en;
skos:prefLabel "Telecommunications"@en;
dct:description "This topic focuses on public policy, regulation, and institutional governance of communication systems, including telecommunications, postal services, radio and television broadcasting, and satellite communications. The representative documents mainly consist of parliamentary debates, legislative measures, and government oversight related to telecom operators, public broadcasting (RAI), postal service reforms, access to information, and regulatory authorities. Overall, the topic reflects how communication and information services are managed at the national policy level."@en;
skos:altLabel "Media and Telecommunications"@en,"Public Communications"@en,"Telecommunications Policy"@en,"Media and Information Services"@en .
