tm:topic_5 a tm:Topic;
rdfs:comment "A topic is a FrAC observation that groups observable lexical forms (OntoLex Forms) and is observed in a corpus."@en;
skos:prefLabel "Terrorism"@en;
dct:description "This topic centers on political debate, legislation, and state action against terrorism. It includes discussions on the definition of terrorism, terrorist acts such as kidnappings and political violence, police powers, criminal penalties, civil liberties, and the balance between repression and democratic rights. The representative documents reflect parliamentary confrontations over anti-terrorism laws from the ?Years of Lead? through to more recent international and domestic counterterrorism efforts, highlighting both security strategies and concerns about legal overreach."@en;
skos:altLabel "Counterterrorism Policy"@en,"Anti-Terrorism Legislation"@en,"Terrorism and State Security"@en,"Internal Security Policy"@en .
