tm:topic_6 a tm:Topic;
rdfs:comment "A topic is a FrAC observation that groups observable lexical forms (OntoLex Forms) and is observed in a corpus."@en;
skos:prefLabel "Cultural entertainment"@en;
dct:description "This topic concerns public policy, regulation, and political debate surrounding cinema, theater, music, and cultural production. It includes issues such as state funding for films and theaters, censorship and age ratings, licensing and co-productions, public oversight of artistic content, and the role of cultural institutions in tourism and national identity. The representative documents reflect parliamentary scrutiny of film production, cultural subsidies, public broadcasting, and the governance of major artistic institutions."@en;
skos:altLabel "Cultural and Performing Arts Policy"@en,"Cultural Policy and Cinema"@en,"Arts and Entertainment Regulation"@en,"Film and Theater Policy"@en .
