rdfs:comment "A topic is a FrAC observation that groups observable lexical forms (OntoLex Forms) and is observed in a corpus."@en;
skos:prefLabel "Linguistic minorities"@en;
dct:description "This topic concerns the legal, political, and institutional protection of linguistic minorities in Italy. It focuses on debates about minority languages (such as German, Ladin, Friulian, Sardinian), bilingualism and multilingualism in public institutions, education, and regional governance?especially in autonomous areas like the Province of Bolzano and regions with special statutes. The documents reflect parliamentary discussions on balancing the recognition of Italian as the official language with the constitutional and European obligation to safeguard historical linguistic communities."@en;
skos:altLabel "Linguistic Minorities"@en,"Minority Language Protection"@en,"Language Rights Policy"@en,"Bilingualism and Autonomy"@en .
