tm:topic_15 a tm:Topic;
rdfs:comment "A topic is a FrAC observation that groups observable lexical forms (OntoLex Forms) and is observed in a corpus."@en;
skos:prefLabel "Catholic teaching"@en;
dct:description "This topic covers the relationship between religion?especially Catholicism?and the Italian state, with a strong focus on religious instruction in public schools. It includes parliamentary debates on the Concordat and its revisions, agreements (intese) with religious confessions, the legal status of religion teachers, the optional nature of Catholic religious education, and the balance between secular principles and religious freedom. More broadly, it reflects state?church relations and the role of religion in public education and cultural life."@en;
skos:altLabel "Religion and Education"@en,"Church–State Relations"@en,"Religious Education Policy"@en,"Catholicism in Schools"@en .
