tm:topic_38 a tm:Topic;
rdfs:comment "A topic is a FrAC observation that groups observable lexical forms (OntoLex Forms) and is observed in a corpus."@en;
skos:prefLabel "Oncology Healthcare"@en;
dct:description "This topic revolves around discussions of healthcare policies, medical research, and patient care related to cancer. It includes issues such as access to treatment, clinical trials, experimental therapies, healthcare infrastructure, and the role of medical professionals and institutions in managing oncological diseases. The documents reflect parliamentary debates addressing both patient needs and regulatory considerations for cancer care."@en;
skos:altLabel "Cancer Treatment Policy"@en,"Oncology and Healthcare"@en,"Cancer Research and Therapy"@en,"Medical Policy for Tumors"@en .
