tm:topic_44 a tm:Topic;
rdfs:comment "A topic is a FrAC observation that groups observable lexical forms (OntoLex Forms) and is observed in a corpus."@en;
skos:prefLabel "Environmental and climate issues"@en;
dct:description "This topic centers on international efforts to combat climate change, particularly through the Kyoto Protocol. It addresses issues such as greenhouse gas emissions, environmental protection, European and national policies, implementation challenges, and debates on Italy?s compliance and commitments. The discussions reflect both political and technical aspects of reducing emissions and mitigating global warming."@en;
skos:altLabel "Kyoto Climate Policy"@en,"Greenhouse Gas Regulation"@en,"Climate Change Legislation"@en,"Environmental Policy Kyoto"@en .
